{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|阜|夌|ls=ic|ls2=psc|c1=s|c2=p|t1=mound|t2=mound; hill}}. Originally written {{zh-l|*夌}}.

===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|alt=夌,䧙,𨻪,𨻎,𨹧,𠡭}}

; "mound; hill; gravemound of an emperor"
: Compare {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*m-raŋ||high; long}}, whence {{cog|my|မြင့်||high; tall}} (STEDT). Also compare {{och-l|嶺|mountain ridge}}.
; "to mount; to transgress; to encroach upon"
: The same word as {{och-l|凌|to rise high; to transgress}}. May be related to the etymology above ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). It is probably cognate with {{och-l|馮|id=1|to cross; to mount; to wade}}.

