===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|みささぎ|yomi=k}}
First part is likely {{ja-r|御|み-|pos=honorific prefix used in relation to gods, emperors, etc.}}; compare {{ja-r|宮|みや|[[shrine]], [[temple]]; [[imperial]] [[palace]]; [[member]] of the imperial [[family]], [[prince]]}}, from {{ja-com|nocat=y|御|み-|屋|や|t2=[[house]]}} and {{ja-r|帝|みかど|[[emperor]]}}, from {{ja-com|nocat=y|御|み-|門|かど|t2=[[gate]]}}.

The derivation of the second part is uncertain; compare {{ja-r|捧ぐ|ささぐ}}, {{w|Classical Japanese}} form of modern {{ja-r|捧げる|ささげる|to [[give]]; to [[offer]], to [[sacrifice]]; to [[dedicate]], to [[devote]]}}.

